    PropertyValueSource, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String>
    public class PropertyMap
extends VariableMap<java.lang.String>
    A property map is a VariableMap with strings as both keys and values.

    Creating and Loading Property Maps

    A property map can be created or loaded from a Resource with:

    • create() - Creates an empty property map
    • of(VariableMap) - Creates a property map from the given variable map
    • load(Resource) - Loads property map from the given resource
    • localized(PackagePath, Locale) - Loads a property map from the given package with a relative path from the given Locale of the form "locales/[language-name](/[country-name])?.

    Conversions

    • copy() - A copy of this property map
    • asObject(Listener, Class) - Creates a new instance of the given class and populates its properties with the values in this property map using ObjectPopulator
    • asInt(String) - The given value as an int
    • asLong(String) - The given value as a long
    • asDouble(String) - The given value as a double
    • asCount(String) - The given value as a Count

    Adding to Property Maps

    In addition to the methods inherited from VariableMap, property maps add the following methods:

    • comment(String, String) - Attaches the given comment to the given key
    • add(Object, PropertyFilter) - Adds the properties of the given object that match the filter to this map

    Saving Property Maps

    • save(WritableResource) - Saves this property map to the given resource
    • save(String, WritableResource) - Saves this property map to the given resource with the given heading
